      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The marketplace of ideas posits that truth will ultimately triumph over falsehood when all ideas are allowed to compete openly. To censor misinformation or hate speech, even if repugnant, is to grant the state the power to decide what is true, which is an inherently dangerous act of authoritarianism. Allowing these ideas to be countered by better, more truthful arguments in the public square is the only mechanism that preserves genuine intellectual freedom.",
