      "content": "The defense against algorithmic manipulation rests on the belief that the solution to bad speech is more speech, not enforced silence. While algorithms present challenges, the philosophical response is to treat them as a technological problem to be overcome with better digital literacy and critical thinking, not a justification for state censorship. Allowing the market to correct itself through overwhelming counter-narratives is the only defense against the government co-opting the role of arbiter of truth.",
